# Banner Management Module Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the steps to build the Banner Management module in the Admin Panel, including database schema updates, backend POST endpoint for secure uploads, and the frontend management UI.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> The backend POST endpoint requires `firebase-admin` to securely upload images to Firebase Storage from the server and verify admin privileges. Since `firebase-admin` is not currently in the root [package.json](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/project%20%281%29/package.json), I will install it via `npm i firebase-admin` in the root directory.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Changes
#### [MODIFY] [schema.gql](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/project%20(1)/dataconnect/schema/schema.gql)
- Add `Banner` table definition:
```graphql
type Banner @table {
  imageUrl: String!
  linkUrl: String
  altText: String
  isActive: Boolean!
}
```

---

### Backend Components
#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/project%20(1)/src/app/api/admin/banners/route.ts)
- Implement `POST` endpoint to handle `multipart/form-data`.
- Extract text fields (link_url, alt_text, is_active) and the image file.
- Validate that the requesting user is an Admin using `verifyIdToken` and checking against the `adminUsers` Firestore collection or checking `SUPER_ADMIN_UID`.
- Upload the image buffer to Firebase Storage using `firebase-admin` to a dedicated `banners/` path.
- Save the metadata parameters + `imageUrl` to the Data Connect `Banner` table by executing a GraphQL mutation directly or via the DataConnect client.

---

### Frontend Components
#### [MODIFY] [sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/project%20(1)/src/app/admin/components/sidebar.tsx)
- Add a new navigation item for "Banners" linking to `/admin/banners`.

#### [NEW] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/project%20(1)/src/app/admin/banners/page.tsx)
- Create a UI to manage banners.
- Display a form with an explicit instruction message: "Images should be optimized for 1376x448 pixels."
- The form will accept an image file, `link_url`, `alt_text`, and an initial `is_active` toggle.
- Submitting the form posts `FormData` to the `/api/admin/banners` endpoint.
- Include a list/table section displaying existing banners, with a toggle button to switch `is_active` on or off.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
Currently, there doesn't seem to be an automated test suite. If desired, API endpoints can be unit-tested, but I will focus on manual verification for this UI-heavy feature.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the project in the browser and navigate to `/admin/login` and sign in.
2. Verify that the "Banners" sidebar link appears and routes successfully to `/admin/banners`.
3. Try uploading a banner through the form on the Banners page and submit. Observe any success/error toasts.
4. Verify the newly uploaded banner image is visible in Firebase Storage and the metadata appears in the Data Connect database.
5. In the UI list, toggle the `is_active` state on/off and verify the UI updates accordingly and saves the state to the backend.
6. Attempt to hit the `/api/admin/banners` endpoint with a non-admin token or an unauthenticated request to verify the security constraints correctly block access.
